      "policy_language_requires_deescalation": "Category: Requires Deescalation\nCity Policy: Police Department Policy Manual\nImpact on Police Violence: Requires officers to use de-escalation when possible. \nPolicy Language: It is the policy of the Elk Grove to de-escalate crisis situations without the use of force whenever possible. Officers are expected to use de-escalation techniques in an effort to reduce the need for and/or the level of force required. Further, officers should not use tactics which create an exigency resulting in less time to decide on the proper level of force, or necessitates the use of an increased level of force.",
