      "policy_language_requires_deescalation": "Category: Requires Deescalation\nCity Policy: Police Department Policy Manual\nImpact on Police Violence: Requires officers to use de-escalation when possible. \nPolicy Language: Officers shall attempt to control an incident by using time, distance, communications, and available resources in an effort to de-escalate the situation, whenever it is safe and reasonable to do so.",
      "bans_chokeholds_and_strangleholds": 1,
      "policy_language_bans_chokeholds_and_strangleholds": "Category: Bans Chokeholds and Strangleholds\nCity Policy: Police Department Policy Manual\nImpact on Police Violence: Department Policy bans chokeholds in all cases and bans strangleholds except for cases when deadly force is authorized. \nPolicy Language: Bans referenced in media reports: http://www.nationaljournal.com/congress/2014/12/10/why-many-large-police-departments-tolerate-their-officers-using-neck-holds and http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-chokehold-20141210-story.html .",
      "duty_to_intervene": 1,
      "policy_language_duty_to_intervene": "Category: Duty to Intervene\nCity Policy: Police Department Policy Manual\nImpact on Police Violence: Requires police to intervene and report when witnessing excessive force. \nPolicy Language: Section 3/813.05: Requires that when an employee, at any level, becomes aware of possible misconduct by another member of this Department, the employee shall immediately report the incident to a supervisor or directly to Internal Affairs Group. Furthermore, an employee who observes serious misconduct shall take appropriate action to cause the misconduct to immediately cease. The fact that a supervisor is present and not taking appropriate action to stop the misconduct does not relieve other employees present from this obligation.",
      "requires_warning_before_shooting": 0,
