      "restricts_shooting_at_moving_vehicles": 1,
      "policy_language_restricts_shooting_at_moving_vehicles": "Category: Bans Shooting at Moving Vehicles\nCity Policy: Police Department Policy Manual\nImpact on Police Accountability: Prohibits officers from shooting at moving vehicles except when someone uses deadly force against officers or another person by means other than the vehicle.\nPolicy Language: Firearms shall not be discharged at a moving vehicle unless a person in the vehicle is immediately threatening the officer or another person with deadly force by means other than the vehicle. The moving vehicle itself shall not presumptively constitute a threat that justifies an officers use of deadly force. An officer threatened by an oncoming vehicle shall move out of its path instead of discharging a firearm at it or any of its occupants.",
      "requires_comprehensive_reporting": 0,
      "policy_language_requires_comprehensive_reporting": "Category: Requires Comprehensive Use of Force Reporting\nCity Policy: Police Department Policy Manual\nImpact on Police Accountability: Does not require officers to report when they point a firearm at a civilian.\nPolicy Language: Officers not required to report when they point a firearm at a civilian.",
      "requires_exhaust_other_means_before_shooting": 0,
      "policy_language_requires_exhaust_other_means_before_shooting": "Category: Requires Exhaust All Other Means Before Shooting\nCity Policy: Police Department Policy Manual\nImpact on Police Accountability: Does not require officers to use reasonable alternatives before using deadly force. Instead, Department Policy allows officers to use deadly force whenever they \"reasonably\" believe there to be an imminent threat, even if reasonable alternatives such as non-lethal force could have been effectively used instead.\nPolicy Language: LAPD Deadly Force Policy: Law enforcement officers are authorized to use deadly force to: \n\"- Protect themselves or others from what is reasonably believed to be an imminent threat of death or serious bodily injury; or,\n- Prevent a crime where the suspect's actions place person(s) in imminent jeopardy of death or serious bodily injury; or,\n- Prevent the escape of a violent fleeing felon when there is probable cause to believe the escape will pose a significant threat of death or serious bodily injury to the officer or others if apprehension is delayed. In this circumstance, officers shall, to the extent practical, avoid using deadly force that might subject innocent bystanders or hostages to possible death or injury.",
