      "policy_language_restricts_shooting_at_moving_vehicles": "Category: Bans Shooting at Moving Vehicles\nCity Policy: Sheriff's Department Policy Manual \nImpact on Police Violence: \"Discourages\" but does not ban officers from shooting at moving vehicles even when the vehicle itself is considered the only threat. The <a href=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/sep/01/moving-targets-police-shootings-vehicles-the-counted> federal government, activists and even law enforcement groups have recommended that this practice be banned because it endangers lives.\nPolicy Language: A. AUTHORIZED DISCHARGE OF FIREARMS POLICY\nB. GENERAL\n2. Discharging a firearm at or from a moving vehicle is rarely effective and is generally discouraged.",
