      "requires_comprehensive_reporting": 0,
      "policy_language_requires_comprehensive_reporting": "No.\n  While new changes to NYPD use of force policy will require reporting of most interactions, they will not require reporting of all incidents where officers point their firearms at civilians or put somebody up against a wall as per http://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/01/nyregion/new-york-police-will-document-virtually-all-instances-of-force.html",
