      "policy_language_bans_chokeholds_and_strangleholds": "No. Carotid Control Holds authorized as an intermediate force option below deadly force. \"As a defensive or control measure, the carotid restraint may be utilized by a police officer when his/her safety or the safety of another person is threatened. This restraint should be used cautiously and should be used when attempts of lesser force have been exhausted, are ineffective, or would have been inappropriate to attempt.",
