      "requires_comprehensive_reporting": 0,
      "policy_language_requires_comprehensive_reporting": "No. Pointing a weapon at a civilian is not required to be reported. \"A report must be submitted whenever an employee takes an action that results in, or is alleged to have resulted in, injury or death of another person. This report will be either a Use of Force Report, an Interoffice Correspondence, or a statement to the Detective Division as outlined in this policy. If serious bodily injury or an injury that could result in death occurs, this report will be completed by Detective Division as outlined in C.6. Field supervisors will ensure that reports on any other injuries are completed.",
      "requires_exhaust_other_means_before_shooting": 0,
      "policy_language_requires_exhaust_other_means_before_shooting": "No. Officers not required to exhaust other reasonable means before resorting to deadly force. The policy does encourage officers to use de-escalation and other tactics to reduce the need for\" using force but does not explicitly require officers to exhaust all reasonable alternatives prior to using deadly force.\n \"The use of unnecessary or excessive force will result in departmental discipline and may create personal liability for the officer with civil and/or criminal penalties. Actions that do not meet the spirit of this policy will neither be condoned nor tolerated merely because the acts were lawful.",
